{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"elliptic-secondbest-nuthatch","description":"## Why\n`canonical_tracker` (`src/rebar/_store/lock.py:81-84`, `os.path.realpath`) is the lock-path\nanchor guaranteeing symlink callers and real-path callers contend on the **same**\n`.ticket-write.lock` (`lock.py:282-285`). VALIDATED: zero test references `canonical_tracker`;\nthe invariant is untested.\n\n## What\nAdd a cross-process test that acquires through the real path and proves a second acquirer\nusing a symlinked path cannot enter until release (and vice versa).\n\n## Scope\n- New test near `tests/unit/test_lock_stale_reclaim.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Acquire via real path in one process; a second acquirer via a symlink to the tracker\n      blocks until release.\n- [ ] The reverse direction (acquire via symlink, contend via real path) also blocks.\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"8f43-b034-d2b9-4d7f","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":3,"tags":["p2","concurrency","lock"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Add canonical_tracker symlink/realpath cross-process lock-identity test"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784824138262001,"uuid":"744599b1-5425-4176-8442-669490eb2d70"}